<P>
TV RATINGS; CBS BEACHES SOME OF THE LAUGHS AT ABC AND NBC 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LEE MARGULIES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The five top-rated shows on TV last week were ABC and NBC sitcoms, but CBS won 
the week overall, thanks in part to a couple of summer dramas set on the 
beaches of Waikiki and Malibu. 
</P>
<P>
 ABC's "Grace Under Fire," the first-year series starring Brett Butler as a 
divorced mother of three, was the No. 1 show, according to the figures released 
Tuesday by the A.C. Nielsen Co.It was seen in about 14.1 million homes. 
</P>
<P>
 CBS' highest-rated program was the Sunday movie, "Jane's House," which ranked 
seventhamong the week's 97 prime-time network programs. But the best news for 
the network was on Thursday, where the premieres of "One West Waikiki" and 
"Hotel Malibu" gave CBS its best rating for a Thursday in summer since Aug. 13, 
1992. 
</P>
<P>
 The dramas didn't beat NBC's "Seinfeld," "Frasier" and "Dateline NBC," but 
they ran a strong second. "One West Waikiki," with Cheryl Ladd, ranked 14th 
overall, while "Hotel Malibu," with Joanna Cassidy, was 21st. Southland Ratings 
</P>
<P>
