<HEADLINE>
<P>
HOLMES WINS, MAY FIGHT ONCE MORE -- POSSIBLY AGAINST FOREMAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Former world heavyweight champion Larry Holmes says he might have one more 
fight in him, possibly against George Foreman, and then he plans to hang up his 
gloves. 
</P>
<P>
 "We don't have too much in this game left -- I realize that," Holmes said 
Tuesday night after winning a unanimous 10-round decision over Jesse 
Ferguson."If I fight again, great. If I don't, so be it. I don't need boxing. 
I've already made my place in history." 
</P>
<P>
 Holmes, 44, who held the title in 1978-85, improved to 61-4, and is 13-1 in 
the second comeback he began in 1991. 
</P>
<P>
 Ferguson, 37, best known for beating Ray Mercer in 1993 after Mercer 
supposedly asked him to take a dive, is 20-13. Many in the crowd of 2,574 booed 
when it was announced that all three judges favored Holmes, 97-94, 96-94, 
99-92. 
</P>
</TEXT>
