<DATE>
<P>
August 10, 1994, Wednesday, Valley Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Metro; Part B; Page 7; Column 5 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
334 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
FATHER DENIS MEEHAN; BENEDICTINE MONK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DAVID E. BRADY, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Father Denis (Molaise) Meehan, a Benedictine monk who joined St. Andrew's 
Abbey at Valyermo in 1963 and spent numerous years as a guest lecturer in 
classic literature at several Southland colleges, has died. He was 79. 
</P>
<P>
 Meehan died Saturday of cardiac arrest at Antelope Valley Hospital Medical 
Center after a lengthy battle with prostate cancer, Abbot Francis Benedict 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 In May, 1963, Meehan joined the monastery at St. Andrew's, which he called 
home for the rest of his life. During his monastic years, Meehan frequently 
left the abbey to teach as a visiting lecturer at the Claremont Graduate 
School, Scripps College, Pomona College and UCLA. From 1970 to 1973, he taught 
at Marymount College in Palos Verdes. 
</P>
<P>
 Meehan also published several religious texts and wrote articles for many 
journals in England and Ireland. 
</P>
<P>
 "He was a lover of nature, an avid bicyclist, walker and sun worshiper," the 
abbot said in a statement. "Cloudy days were not his cup of tea." 
</P>
<P>
 Born Sept. 26, 1914, in Castlebar, Mayo, Ireland, Meehan received bachelor's 
and master's degrees from National University in his native country. He was 
educated for the priesthood at National's Maynooth College and ordained a 
priest in the Irish Diocese of Elphin on June 23, 1940. 
</P>
<P>
 During the 1940s and '50s, Meehan studied in England, France, Greece and Rome 
while teaching classic literature at Maynooth. He came to the United States in 
1958 and taught for five years at Los Angeles' Immaculate Heart College before 
deciding to become a monk. 
</P>
<P>
 Meehan is survived by a brother, Charles Meehan, and a sister, Bridget 
Bullock, both of Ireland. 
</P>
<P>
 A vigil will be held at 8:30 p.m. Thursday and the funeral Mass will be 
celebrated at 11 a.m. Friday at the abbey, 31001 N. Valyermo Road. Burial will 
follow at the abbey's cemetery. Halley-Olsen Funeral Chapel in Palmdale is 
handling the arrangements. 
</P>
<P>
 In lieu of flowers, memorial donations may be made in Meehan's name to the 
abbey, 31001 N. Valyermo Road, Valyermo 93563. 
</P>
</TEXT>
