<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY: TELECOMMUNICATIONS & TECHNOLOGY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Two Computer Firms to Merge: Storage Technology Corp. and Network Systems 
Corp., suppliers of computer storage and data communication systems, said they 
have agreed to merge in a stock swap valued at about $300 million.Storage 
Technology said the merger is believed to be the first of a major computer 
storage provider and a leader in high-performance computer networking products. 
The goal is for users of workstations or personal computers to have access to 
massive amounts of data stored in mainframe computers. The technology to 
facilitate moving data among different systems is Network Systems' enterprise 
routing switch, being developed jointly with Northern Telecom. 
</P>
