<HEADLINE>
<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: LOS ANGELES; $25,000 
REWARD POSTED IN SLAYING OF PASTOR, 81 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Los Angeles City Council posted a $25,000 reward Tuesday for information 
leading to the arrest of suspects in the recent murder of an 81-year-old 
minister and grandmother at her Mid-City apartment. 
</P>
<P>
 Los Angeles Police Department officials asked the council to offer the reward 
to aid their investigation into the death of Blanche Thomas, who was bound, 
gagged and sexually assaulted. 
</P>
<P>
 Detectives said they had run out of leads without identifying a suspect.  
</P>
<P>
 "They believe there is information out in the community that could corroborate 
some of their information and lead to a suspect," Deputy City Atty. Gail 
Weingart said. 
</P>
<P>
 As pastor of the small Mt. Zion Churches United parish in the Mid-City area, 
Thomas worked to comfort the elderly, ease the plight of the homeless and curb 
the spread of illicit drugs. 
</P>
<P>
 Police say that someone entered Thomas' apartment in the 1700 block of South 
La Brea Avenue on July 25 between midnight and dawn. Some items were stolen, 
but police believe that the intruder was more intent on violence than on theft. 
</P>
</TEXT>
