<HEADLINE>
<P>
SANTA CLARITA / ANTELOPE VALLEY; LOOKING FOR A MIRACLE; FUND LAUNCHED IN NAME 
OF BOY WHO HAS BRAIN CANCER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Eight-year-old Michael Hoefflin found himself the center of attention Tuesday 
as a cancer fund and support group was launched in his name, but he didn't seem 
concerned about his condition or impressed with the adults fussing about it. 
</P>
<P>
 The Canyon Country boy has had an unusual form of brain cancer for the past 
two years, and his chances of living much longer are uncertain, at best. But he 
merely squirmed restlessly on his father's lap during an interview on a local 
radio station in which the fund was announced, more interested in returning to 
a computer game in the station's office. 
</P>
<P>
 Chris Hoefflin said his son has been acting like any other 8-year-old because 
he is just beginning to feel symptoms of the disease, believed to be in the 
advanced stages. The elder Hoefflin said he co-founded the Michael Hoefflin 
Chapter of The Neil Bogart Memorial Fund with the hope of providing his son and 
other Santa Clarita cancer, leukemia and AIDS patients with needed care and 
support. 
</P>
<P>
 "Michael needs a miracle at this point," he said. 
</P>
<P>
 The local chapter will raise funds for researchers at Childrens Hospital Los 
Angeles, and act as a support group for Santa Clarita families, Chris Hoefflin 
said. The Neil Bogart fund, named after a record company president who died of 
lymphoma in 1983, provides assistance to 114 hospitals nationwide. 
</P>
<P>
 The fund was launched with a $4,990.33 check from Taekwondo USA, where Michael 
enrolled as a student several weeks ago. Studio owner Ken Lewis said the money 
is the surplus from a $12,900 memorial fund for Veronica Estrada, a children's 
instructor at the studio who was strangled in December. Another instructor is 
on trial on a murder charge in the death. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 "We've really dedicated our lives to the well-being of children and we think 
this is a great way to do that," Lewis told KBET-AM radio broadcaster Kate 
Hayes. 
</P>
<P>
 Donations may be made to The Michael Hoefflin Chapter, c/o KBET radio, 27565 
Sierra Highway, Santa Clarita, CA 91351. For more information call (805) 
250-4100. 
</P>
</TEXT>
