infirmary, KBS said. At least nine Japanese were aboard the domestic flight 
from Seoul, the capital. 
</P>
<P>
 The plane was caught by wind gusts after touching down, witnesses said. The 
pilot tried to abort the landing and take off again, but the airliner skidded 
and crashed, they said. 
</P>
<P>
 Winds were gusting because Typhoon Doug was approaching the Korean peninsula 
when the accident happened, the network said. 
