fund group, confirmed that she has been relieved of her duties. Paul Guenther, 
PaineWebber's president, has taken over the post pending a permanent 
replacement, a company spokeswoman said. The move is the brokerage firm's 
latest attempt to contain the damage from its $268-million bailout of the 
short-term government bond fund, according to Lipper Analytical Services Inc. 
Fensterstock was the latest casualty from the costly and embarrassing rescue of 
the fund, which dabbled in risky securities. 
</P>
