<HEADLINE>
<P>
NO 'PUZZLEWORKS' ON KOCE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ZAN DUBIN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Don't look for "The Puzzleworks" on KOCE Channel 50, Orange County's public 
television station.KOCE is a so-called Limited Use Discount station, explains 
spokeswoman Judith Schaefer. That means it receives discounts on programs 
obtained from the Public Broadcasting Service (PBS) as long as it doesn't take 
more than 40% of its programming from the service. At the moment, Schaefer 
said, KOCE has reached the limit and therefore cannot pick up "Puzzleworks" 
without jeopardizing its fiscal base. 
</P>
<P>
 She noted that the Limited Use Discount regulation is scheduled for national 
re-evaluation this fall. "Many public stations would like to have children's 
programs, like 'Puzzleworks,' exempt" from the regulation, she said.ZAN DUBIN 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Sidebar 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA081094-0210 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 068634 </DOCID>
<SOURCE>
<P>
 Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</SOURCE>
<DATE>
<P>
August 10, 1994, Wednesday, Home Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
