<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEFF BEAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Witold Muller, a 58-year-old commercial real estate broker and general 
contractor, has been appointed to fill a seat on the board of the Capistrano 
Beach County Water District. 
</P>
<P>
 Muller won unanimous board approval last week to fill the seat vacated in June 
by Addison H. DeBoi, who quit after an unsuccessful bid to become a Dana Point 
councilman. 
</P>
<P>
 Bill Meadows, the water district's general manager, said that although Muller 
was appointed to a board term that expires in 1996, he must run for election in 
November for the seat's remaining two years. 
</P>
<P>
 Muller could also choose to seek one of two other seats with full two-year 
terms being contested in November. 
</P>
<P>
 Muller said Monday that he intends to run in November but hasn't decided which 
seat to pursue. 
</P>
<P>
 "I don't think I'd be getting involved for the short term," he said. He said 
he planned to speak with the registrar of voters office about his options. 
</P>
<P>
 Besides Muller, five other board hopefuls applied for the seat, according to 
the water district. JEFF BEAN 
</P>
