MAN ELECTROCUTED AT CONSTRUCTION SITE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 30-year-old construction worker was electrocuted Tuesday night when he came 
in contact with a 480-volt power line while restoring the interior of an office 
building, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 The man, who has not been identified, was working with three other employees 
of Laguna Hills-based Tri-Star Restorations at a building in the 18600 block of 
Jamboree Road, near Dupont Drive, Irvine Police Sgt. Jim Lowder said. 
</P>
