<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 US Facilities Corp.: The Costa Mesa insurance company posted a profit of 
$761,000, or 13 cents a share, for the second quarter. That was down from 
earnings of $1.8 million, or 31 cents a share, for the comparable 1993 
quarter.The company attributed the decline to $1.5 million in expenses related 
to an unsolicited takeover attempt by Fidelity National Financial Inc. and a 
subsequent proxy fight, as well as a one-time restructuring charge of $654,000. 
Revenue showed a gain of 18% to $32.2 million from $27.2 million. Profit for 
the first six months of 1994 dropped to $1.4 million, or 23 cents a share, from 
$3.7 million, or 62 cents a share, for the first half of 1993. Six-month 
revenue rose 18% to $62.7 million from $53.2 million. 
</P>
