<TEXT>
<P>
 Northridge quake -- An Aug. 2 story on 121,000 earthquakes in Southern 
California since the beginning of 1987 gave the wrong number of Northridge 
earthquake aftershocks. As of Aug. 1, there were 9,222 recorded Northridge 
aftershocks, including 49 between magnitude 4.0 and 4.9 and eight magnitude 5.0 
or stronger. 
